    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-03-31T00:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-03-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="692"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d692">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/4933: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="#p_JNT1" type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-03-31T13:00:00+08:00"
                            >March 31, 1932—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 31—3:37 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>My March 29, 5 p.m.</p>
                <p>1. Chinese-Japanese negotiators met at 10 a.m. and commenced discussion of
                    article 2 of draft B, March 27th, which was finally accepted in the general
                    form.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“The Chinese troops will remain in their present positions pending later
                        arrangements upon the reestablishment of normal conditions in the areas
                        dealt with by this agreement. The aforesaid positions are indicated in annex
                        1 to this agreement.”</p>
                </quote>
                <p>While the Chinese delegate recorded with the conference the following official
                    declaration: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“It is understood that nothing in this agreement implies any permanent
                            restrictions on the movements of Chinese troops in Chinese
                            territory”.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>2. Next meeting takes place Saturday, April 2nd.</p>
                <p>3. Negotiations threatened to break on the question of date of Japanese
                    withdrawal. It was finally agreed privately between <persName corresp="#p_LSMW1"
                        >Sir Miles</persName> and myself, <persName corresp="#p_SM1"
                        >Shigemitsu</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_QT1">Quo</persName>, to
                    meet informally outside of the conference, <persName corresp="#p_CCG1"
                        >Ciano</persName> and Lagarde participating, to explore possibilities of a
                    formula.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_JNT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
